Text.Value: But we ain't need glory - just coin. And Nere's got plenty.
*The slightest of breezes slips through your skull.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Not a mindmeld but a resonance due to duergar's psionic sensitivity.

Text.Value: The stench don't lie. You're one of them.
What gold? I thought you hadn't been paid yet.
Her crew know more than they're letting on - see if you can get 'em to talk.
A stench? Ridiculous. I'm no more a True Soul than you are.
Some days back, a slave gnome bolted with smokepowder. Handy stuff.
You want my gold? Then you'll have to fight me for it.
You're imagining things. I would never bow to the Absolute.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: this node for those who don't have REALLY_DEEPGNOME

Text.Value: That 'stench' is just psionic resonance - a remnant of our ancestors' enslavement by illithids.
Ain't my gold I'm offering. It's the True Soul's.
Hm... revenge, eh?
I was a True Soul. That cult lied to me - now I want revenge.
You don't leave 'til I get my due.
Time we took our due. Your blade ready, Kur?
Would you look at that, Kur. Someone's having a listen.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Brithvar turns and notices player. Addressed to Kur, looking at player

Text.Value: The cult watches through it. And we can't risk more Twat-Souls showing up.
Thrinn's after the Absolute's glory - that's why she's got those slaves digging for Nere.
Now move. You're hogging my air.
Why would you think I'm a True Soul?
Off with you. Private conversation.
Big words - let's see you back them up.
Please. I've already got more coin than you could carry.
Yet you got that Twat-Soul stench.
These True Souls are my enemies, not my allies.
It was a joke. I'm as poor as a pauper.
If you're offering me a job, I'm not interested.
Half? Drugnin' rakkah. Should split your skull for the insult.
Fine. Half it is.
The stench - all you Twat-Souls got one. Some of us got a nose for it.
He stinks to the deepest hells, that's for sure. Could be you're right.
Any ideas on getting Nere out?

EditorData.logicalname: Player didn't ask about a lead

Text.Value: *The shiver returns. This time, it's colder. Sharper.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Not a mindmeld but a resonance due to duergar's psionic sensitivity.

Text.Value: Fine. Half it is. But you need to bust Nere out first.
Leave.
Could be you're right. Something's different with you.
Fine - I'm a True Soul. What do you plan to do about it?
Fine. Half it is. But first we need to take care of something.

EditorData.NodeContext: Calms himself down with a sigh.

Text.Value: Leave.
Once you blast Nere out, we'll chop him into chunks and take our dues.
I've obtained explosive powder. That should open the tunnel.
Just smile. Let him see the rage in your eyes.
I ain't parleying with more Twat-Souls - that stench don't lie.
You don't need to ask twice. Your blade ready, Kur?
I heard you talking. I want Nere out - and you have a lead.

EditorData.logicalname: Didn't already ask about the lead

Text.Value: In that case - want to earn some gold?
Use your head - can you imagine a deep gnome being picked as a True Soul?
That right? And wouldn't you know - my pockets are mighty light.
Help Thrinn free Nere - then you and my chums grind him up.
Fine. Spill what you want, True Soul, before I choke on your stench.
Good. Reckon the gnomes are key to busting Nere out.
Just what I like to hear.
That's not me you smell. You must still be catching Nere's scent.
Knife it. And don't get caught.
What I am matters not. You seek retribution - I want to help.
Drugnin' True Souls. Can still smell Nere from behind that damned wall.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mind reading node, no lip sync
EditorData.VFXTags: Might need mind reading VFX (Wisnu I)

Text.Value: Seen her run with a barrel under her arm. Just a small one, but enough to blow the drow out.
Whatever the spoils, we'll drop you a fat cut. You in?
A shitty joke, too - I ain't hearing no laughs. Now you want gold or not?
Half? You drugnin'...

EditorData.NodeContext: Rising anger. About to say DRUG-nin RAK-kah. 'Fucking tool'

Text.Value: Good plan. I think Sergeant Thrinn should know about it.
I ain't parleying with more Twat-Souls. And you got the stench.
I want Nere out - and it sounds like you have a lead.
You seen that weird orb-eye floatin' about?
Good. Drop it near the rubble when it's time. Flaming arrow or some such'll set it off.
*A shiver runs through you. Your mind is awash in ancient resentments.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Not a mindmeld but a resonance due to duergar's psionic sensitivity.

Text.Value: Go on, try it. I've been itching for a fight.
Depends. What do you need done?
No clue where the stump's hiding. But she's got what you need.
Shut your trap, Kur. The rakkah's got gold for grabbing.
If I didn't know better, I'd say a mind flayer shat a worm in your brain.
Cast Detect Thoughts.
Someone should grab it. Slaves are never gonna manage with pickaxes.
Don't be absurd. I hate these True Soul cultists.
I ain't parleying with more Twat-Souls - just want my coin. Your blade ready, Kur?
Drop it, Brithvar. You chop this one, and Nere won't pay a damned copper.
Should split your head open and poke around in there if you lot don't pay up.
You still standing about? Get on it!
Done and done.
You want my coin? Just try and take it.
Brithvar. Unwad your britches.
Ain't fooling me. Only you Absolute-lickers get my mind wobbling.
Good. But first we need to take care of something.
Count me out.
Brithvar.

EditorData.NodeContext: A warning - telling Brithvar to shut up.

Text.Value: Gh'rack. Get you gone, before I get you gone.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighs, was hoping to rob the player. GRACK = dammit.

Text.Value: Fair point. Pipsqueak like you is hardly gonna inspire fear and awe, are you?
I feel you poking around. And I'll have your head for it!
Drugnin' shithead - like hell she should!
In that case, I got a proposal. Want to earn some gold?
I'm worth more than a 'cut'. I want half.
I'm in.
I asked about a lead. And you still haven't answered.

EditorData.logicalname: Player insisted there was a lead.

Text.Value: Sounds good. I expect half the spoils.
True Soul, no less. What do you think, Kur - should we take Nere's debt off him?
True Soul, no less. What do you think, Kur - should we take Nere's debt off her?
True Soul, no less. What do you think, Kur - should we take Nere's debt off them?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to Kur, looking at player

Text.Value: Can't go chasing 'maybes' - the sergeant's our ticket in.
All I'm going to spill are your guts.
Collect my due pay for starters. Blade ready, Kur?

Synopsis:
Two duergar consider how their fellow duergar have fallen for this new cult that showed up. You can inspire in them a mutiny. If you do, they'll join you when you free Nere (UND_TheDrowNere_Mutiny).

Brithvar is a Mind Master, a duergar with psionic skills. He wears a strange mask.
